		h1.page-title Helpers

		article.article.introduction
			p Helper classes can help remove repetition by creating a set of abstract classes that can be used over and over on HTML elements. Each helper class is responsible for doing one job and doing it well. Doing this will make your code more reusable and scalable. 

			p All helper classes use the !important flag to avoid specificity issues. 

		article.article
			h2 Background Color
			p Generates a background-color helper for all colors specified in your $colours map, in the following format: background-{$category}-{$value}.
			.example
				div.background-brand-primary(style="height: 40px")
				div.background-secondary-orange(style="height: 40px")
				div.background-greyscale-50(style="height: 40px")
			pre
				code.language-html.
					&lt;div class="background-brand-primary"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
					&lt;div class="background-secondary-orange"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
					&lt;div class="background-greyscale-50"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

		article#borders.article
			h2#borders Borders
			p Adds or removes a keyline to a given element. The border color used is the keyline value specified in your <span class="var">$colours</span> map.
			table
				tr
					td border-left
				tr
					td border-top
				tr
					td border-right
				tr
					td border-bottom
				tr
					td border-all
				tr
					td no-border

			.example 

			pre
				code.language-scss
					| .border-bottom {
					|  border-bottom: 1px solid #F5F5F5 !important;
					| }

		article.article(id="margin")
			h2 Margin & Padding
			p Allows your to add or remove margin or padding in all directions, or a given direction. These are generated using the values stored in the <span class="var">$sizes</span> map.

			table
				tr
					td .padding-{direction}-{size}
					td Applies padding in the specified direction of the specified size.
				tr
					td .margin-{direction}-{size}
					td Applies padding in the specified direction of the specified size.
				tr
					td .no-margin
					td Removes all margins
				tr
					td .no-padding
					td Removes all padding

			.example
				div.background-brand-primary.margin-bottom-quarter(style="height: 40px")
				div.background-brand-primary.margin-bottom-base(style="height: 40px")

			pre
				code.language-html.
					&lt;div class="margin-bottom-double"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
					&lt;div class="margin-base"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
					&lt;div class="padding-left-half"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

